RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 1 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $1,50 0 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALL stalked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, gained ground three wide heading to the quarter pole, made a steady gain on TWO TWELVE into mid-stretch, took command into the final sixteenth and kicked clear to prevail. TWO TWELVE was sent in the opening furlong, established the lead in the early running while outside of runners and set a solid pace while off of the rail along the turn, held ALL at bay into upper stretch, was overtaken by that rival into the final sixteenth, could not match strides with the winner into deep stretch and bested the rest. HOW ABOUT A FRESCA broke in at the start and was off a step slowly, settled off of the solid early pace and tracked from the inside along the turn, gained ground into the stretch, was not able to impact the top two in deep stretch and ran on to secure third. MISCHIEF MAMA stalked the solid early pace, came in tight approaching the turn while between runners and checked, stalked the pace three to four wide into the stretch, weakened and was outfinished for third. SEVEN SISTERS broke alertly, lost the early lead to TWO TWELVE, chased that rival through solid fractions while saving ground along the turn, came two wide into the stretch and gave way. COASTAL STARLITE lacked early speed, chased three wide into the lane and did not threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: How About a Fresca
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in start,tracked inside,stretch bid,ran on for 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Seven Sisters
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,chased inside,2wide into stretch,gave way

ENTRY.OWNER: Martin Jill A McDonald Frank and McDonald Melanie

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A LOTTA NERVE was hard to load prior to the start and broke a half-step slowly away from the gate, recovered and assumed command in the opening stages, showed speed and opened to a clear lead into the turn, extended the lead while off of the rail heading to the quarter marker, widened the lead into mid-stretch and drew off in the final furlong in an impressive debut win. SOUTHERN BLESSING rook back off of the solid early pace, was steered three wide into the stretch, was not able to impact the winner in the final stages and ran on to secure the place. AUTISM SHINE chased the fast pace from the inside, raced in tight along the turn and steadied nearing the quarter marker, maintained an inside path into upper stretch, lacked the needed response in the final furlong but stayed on in deep stretch to secure third. FOREVER LOVELY stalked the fast pace from a two wide path, chased A LOTTA NERVE into the stretch, could not keep pace into the final furlong and faded. ESCAPE THE HEAT chased the fast early pace, lost ground while two wide along the turn, dropped back into upper stretch and tired in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: A Lotta Nerve
ENTRY.COMMENT: hard to load,sent,showed speed 2p,drew off stretch,good debut

ENTRY.NAME: Southern Blessing
ENTRY.OWNER: Berger Jeffrey and Valenzuela Thomas N
ENTRY.COMMENT: took back,roused 3wide,no match for winner,ran on 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AYRTON SENNA broke alertly, ceded the early lead to TEAGANS ATM and stalked that rivals through decent early fractions, was roused from the three path at the top of the stretch, drew to even terms with TEAGANS ATM nearing the furlong marker, took command from that rival and drove clear in the final sixteenth. TEAGANS ATM assumed command in the early going, set decent fractions into the turn, drifted out a bit at the top of the lane and came two wide into the stretch, was confronted nearing the furlong pole by AYRTON SENNA, was overtaken and could not match strides with that rival into the final sixteenth, was outfinished and held safely in the end for second. BRONZE ONE raced close to the decent early pace, saved ground to the top of the lane, offered a mild bid at the furlong marker, was outkicked into deep stretch and held well in the final stages for third. ZHIVAGO chased the decent early pace while outside of rivals, raced three wide to the quarter pole, lost ground into the stretch and lacked a late rally. COBRE bobbled leaving the break and was off a bit slowly, settled off of the decent early pace and came two wide into the turn, was steered four wide into the lane and did not threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Teagans Atm
ENTRY.OWNER: Baker D Wayne Porlaris Reynaldo and Santoro Michele

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 12500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FANTASTIC DREAM was allowed to settle, tracked the decent early pace while two wide and between runners along the first turn, was well placed heading to the half-mile marker, was roused three wide and between runners approaching the quarter pole, vied for the lead into upper stretch and battled with L L L COOL to the furlong marker, took command into the final stages, held the runner-up at bay into deep stretch and kept to task in the end to prevail. L L L COOL was prominent in the early running and contested the pace into the first turn, prompted the pace from a two wide path into the backstretch run, kept close attendance to the decent pace to the half-mile marker, took command while two wide and between runners approaching the quarter marker, was confronted by FANTASTIC DREAM into upper stretch and battled with that rival to mid-stretch, lost the lead into the final furlong, was held at bay in deep stretch and was clear of the rest for second. BRANNIGAN settled outside of runners into the first turn, raced three wide into the backstretch run and improved position heading to the half-mile marker, mounted a four wide bid at the quarter marker, ran evenly to the furlong grounds, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was outkicked, while well clear of the rest for third. VINNIEBOB was asked for early speed and assumed command into the first turn, crossed over to the inside and set decent fractions into the backstretch run, carved out the pace to the half-mile marker, was overtaken nearing the quarter marker and faded in the stretch. STELLA BOY was forwardly placed away from the gate, stalked the decent early pace from the inside, lost position nearing the half-mile marker, lost contact along the second turn, was eased through the stretch and walked off under his own power.

ENTRY.NAME: Brannigan
ENTRY.OWNER: Perez Sergio S and Abrahamson Joe

ENTRY.NAME: Fantastic Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: never far back,asked btwn 3wide 1/4,battled upper,held driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (If A Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive A $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association)(Non-sta rters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JERSEY SUNSET broke alertly and showed speed away from the gate, set a moderate pace prompted into the turn, shook free along the bend and was well rated to the quarter marker setting the pace off of the rail, showed the way into upper stretch and held a safe lead approaching the furlong grounds, was all out to hold off BERRY VALLEY inside of the sixteenth-marker, was fully extended in the final strides and lasted for the win at the finish. BERRY VALLEY stalked the moderate early pace outside of rivals, was well placed three wide approaching the quarter pole, responded to urging three wide into the stretch, came within aim in the final sixteenth and just missed for the win, besting the rest. ADAPTED MEMORY tracked the moderate early pace from the inside, saved ground to the quarter marker, ran evenly to mid-stretch, was outkicked by the top pair in the final furlong and held clearly for third. SURFLINE raced close to the early pace, mildly pressed outside of JERSEY SUNSET into the turn and chased two wide to the quarter pole, angled four wide in the stretch and did not offer a late response. TIZTHEHARTOFDIXIE chased the pace from the inside and did not threaten. HARBOR'S BEAUTY was a bit slow into stride away from the gate, was outrun along the turn and did not factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Harbor's Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow into stride,void early speed,outrun turn,no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Adapted Memory
ENTRY.OWNER: Stubblefield Thomas B and Stubblefield Susan

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 83. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 12500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THREAD COUNT contested the early pace away from the gate, took back and tracked the decent pace from the inside, was roused along the turn, shifted out and made a three wide move approaching the quarter marker, battled with BIG MAMA THORNTON into upper stretch and lost a bit of ground to that rival nearing the furlong pole, re-rallied into deep stretch, vied between rivals in the final yards and gamely prevailed at the finish. NAN ELIZABETH bobbled at the start, was off a step slowly and was unhurried in the early stages, came three wide into the turn, raced wide into the stretch and was asked for run from the six path at the top of the lane, ran evenly to the furlong marker, closed with a rush while widest in deep stretch, vied for the lead in the final strides and just missed for the win while just earning the nod for the place. BIG MAMA THORNTON contested the early pace while outside of a pair of rivals then dueled with JASMINE CHIEFTAIN into the turn, carved out moderate fractions from the two path approaching the quarter marker, shook free into upper stretch and was kept to steady urging to the furlong marker, held a narrow lead into the final sixteenth, was all out to hold off oncoming rivals in deep stretch, was outfinished by the top two in the final strides and was clear for third. JASMINE CHIEFTAIN was prominent in the early running, disputed the early pace while between runners then pressed BIG MAMA THORNTON while inside of that rival heading into the turn, lost position heading to the quarter marker, saved ground into upper stretch and remained within range at the furlong grounds, chased into deep stretch and lacked a final response.

ENTRY.NAME: Jasmine Chieftain
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside,lost position 1/4,chased stretch,no final kick

ENTRY.NAME: Nan Elizabeth
ENTRY.OWNER: Gabriel Luciano Medina and Zhu Xuewen

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 86. Starter Allowance Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. One win for $25,000 or less not considered.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHARONA'S WILD BOY broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, was engaged by ELCONDOR and disputed the quick early pace with that rival heading into the turn, rated entering the turn and tracked while saving ground heading to the quarter marker, re-bid in upper stretch and vied for the lead at the furlong pole, dueled with ELCONDOR into the final sixteenth and took command in deep stretch, dug in and kept to task to the finish to prevail. ELCONDOR broke in at the start and bumped WESTERN CAPE, was hustled to be prominent in the early running and disputed the solid early pace with SHARONA'S WILD BOY, shook free of that rival entering the turn and rated along the bend to carve out moderate fractions at the quarter marker, was confronted by SHARONA'S WILD BOY in upper stretch and battled with that rival to the furlong grounds, dueled into the final sixteenth, was held at bay in deep stretch and was clear of the rest for second. WORTH LOOKING broke a step slowly away from the start and was allowed to settle early on, raced two wide into the turn, was roused four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, was not able to impact the top two in the final sixteenth but closed well and was up in time to secure third. THREEBROTHERS stalked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, mounted a three wide bid approaching the quarter marker, could not sustain his bid into the stretch, flattened out in the late stages and was outfinished for third. WESTERN CAPE was bumped at the start and was off a step slowly, recovered and raced close to the fast early pace, came in tight while between runners, steadied off of heels nearing the nine-sixteenths marker and was shuffled back heading to the half-mile pole, chased the leaders into the turn, gained ground while two wide approaching the quarter marker, was outkicked into upper stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Worth Looking
ENTRY.OWNER: Kelly Stables Galloping Bruin Racing TAK Racing and Barry Kevin

ENTRY.NAME: Sharona's Wild Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: disputed early pace,took back turn,re-bid 3/16,dueled,dug in late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 95. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $32,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $32,0 00 (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred)(Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won An Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. Unless Entered For A ClaimingP rice).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS UNION was away in good order and was prominent leaving the start, took back to track the solid early pace and maintained a two wide path into the turn, was roused along the bend and vied for the lead while two wide and between runners nearing the quarter marker, battled for the lead into upper stretch with HOT RAGEOUS, repelled that rival's bid heading to the furlong grounds, kicked clear into deep stretch and drew off in the final stages to win going away. HOT RAGEOUS lunged at the start and was away slowly, settled off of the quick early pace and raced outside of rivals into the turn, loomed four wide approaching the quarter marker and battled for the lead into upper stretch with MISS UNION, was turned away by that rival inside of the furlong pole, was outkicked in deep stretch and held safely in the end for the place. BUYBACK was forwardly placed away from the start and stalked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, improved position into the turn while three deep, came in tight nearing the quarter marker and took up while between runners approaching the top of the stretch, raced four wide into the lane, could not muster the needed response in the final furlong but stayed on in deep stretch and was clear in the end for third. DULCE EMMA stalked the solid early pace from the inside, saved ground into the turn and advanced nearing the quarter marker, came in tight while behind runners and waited for racing room nearing the top of the lane, shifted to the two path into upper stretch, was outrun to the furlong marker and weakened in the final sixteenth. LADY WOLF was hard sent away from the gate, showed good early speed and dictated terms to the half-mile marker, came under pressure heading to the quarter pole, was overtaken into upper stretch and tired in the drive. THE RIDER OF HOT RAGEOUS LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST THE RIDER OF MISS UNION. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Union
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace,bid btwn 2wd 1/4,repelled foe 1/8,drew off late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 9 1M Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $3,50 0 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GORDY'S BOY was caught three wide into the first turn then settled in a tracking spot behind the pace, raced five wide on the outside of the tracking group down the backstretch, started a rally approaching the three furlong marker, took command into the stretch and won clear under brisk handling to the wire. BROKEN FINGER was quick from the break and encouraged to get forward position, then was taken in hand and let FRANKS FIX IT alone on the lead, made a bid on the far turn when that one began to weaken near the three-eighths pole, vied briefly with GORDY'S BOY to the outside but could not match strides with that rival then ran on well to finish second, well clear of the next horse. POUR ON THE COLE secured an inside position and settled mid-pack while the pace scenario played out in front, was put into a drive passing the seven-sixteenths pole then swung five wide into the stretch and was tiring down the stretch but managed hold the third position under steady pressure. BROOKYS TAPIT got squeezed after the break then was taken in hand to be last into the first turn, fell way behind the field for the first half mile then gradually regained contact with the field heading into the far turn, made a three wide rally through the turn that ran out of steam in the stretch, but kept on to improve position in the late going. MARKSMAN ON TARGET raced close up while in the three to four path, began to struggle to keep up by the far turn, lost ground then was not persevered with and ridden out to the finish. BEL RAGAZZO raced near the rear of the tracking group, then set up for a run through the turn then was unable to keep up by the five-sixteenths and was outrun from that point on. FRANKS FIX IT broke in after the start and caused BROOKYS TAPIT to take up, and was sent for the lead with purpose, opened up a big lead through the clubhouse turn, continued to set rapid fractions down the backstretch, still held the lead to the far turn then started to fade passing the three furlong pole.
